  "prompt": "If I am going for an interview for Android developer, what questions should I expect in the technical round?",
  "response": "Here are common Android developer interview questions across different difficulty levels:\n\nBasic Level:\n1. What is Android?\n2. Explain Android architecture\n3. What are the four components of Android?\n4. Difference between Activities and Fragments\n5. What is an Intent?\n6. Explain Activity lifecycle\n7. What is ANR (Application Not Responding)?\n\nIntermediate Level:\n1. Explain Kotlin vs Java in Android development\n2. What is RecyclerView?\n3. Difference between AsyncTask and Coroutines\n4. Explain MVP and MVVM architecture\n5. What are background services?\n6. How do you handle memory leaks?\n7. Explain Dependency Injection\n8. What is Room database?\n9. How do you implement data binding?\n\nAdvanced Level:\n1. Explain Jetpack Compose\n2. How do you optimize app performance?\n3. Implement custom view\n4. Implement multithreading\n5. Architecture components\n6. Implement offline caching\n7. Handling configuration changes\n8. Advanced RxJava concepts\n\nTechnical Skills Assessment:\n1. Live coding challenge\n2. System design\n3. Algorithm problem-solving\n4. Code review\n\nPractical Tips:\n- Know core Android concepts\n- Stay updated with latest technologies\n- Prepare portfolio/GitHub projects\n- Practice coding challenges",
